 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Classical ML Models — IMDB Sentiment Classification\n",
    "\n",
    "**Project:** Building a Transformer Encoder from Scratch: A Comparative Evaluation Against Classical ML Models\n",
    "\n",
    "**Author:** Shoeb Shakil Sutar | PRN: 25070149022 | M.Tech AIML\n",
    "\n",
    "**Description:** This notebook implements four classical ML classifiers (Logistic Regression, Multinomial Naive Bayes, Random Forest, Linear SVC) on the IMDB dataset using both Count Vectorizer and TF-IDF features."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Required Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import nltk\n",
    "nltk.download(\"all\")\n",
    "\n",
    "from nltk.corpus import stopwords\n",
    "from nltk.tokenize import word_tokenize\n",
    "from nltk.stem import WordNetLemmatizer"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import re\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import (\n",
    "    accuracy_score, confusion_matrix,\n",
    "    classification_report, RocCurveDisplay\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Load and Explore Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Note:** Upload `IMDB Dataset.csv` to your Colab session before running.\n",
    "> Download from: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/lakshmi25npathi/imdb-dataset-of-50k-movie-reviews"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = pd.read_csv(\"/content/IMDB Dataset.csv\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Shape of Dataset :\\n\", df.shape)\n",
    "print(\"\\nSize of Dataset :\\n\", df.size)\n",
    "print(\"\\nColumns :\\n\", df.columns.tolist())\n",
    "print(\"\\nNull Values :\\n\", df.isnull().sum())\n",
    "print(\"\\nDuplicated Rows :\", df.duplicated().sum())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Remove duplicate rows\n",
    "df = df.drop_duplicates()\n",
    "print(\"Shape after removing duplicates:\", df.shape)\n",
    "\n",
    "df.head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Text Preprocessing\n",
    "\n",
    "Classical models receive fully preprocessed text:\n",
    "- Lowercase\n",
    "- Remove special characters\n",
    "- Word tokenization\n",
    "- Lemmatization\n",
    "- Stopword removal"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "stop_words = set(stopwords.words(\"english\"))\n",
    "lemmatizer = WordNetLemmatizer()\n",
    "\n",
    "def text_preprocess(text: str) -> str:\n",
    "    \"\"\"Full preprocessing pipeline for classical ML models.\"\"\"\n",
    "    text  = text.lower()\n",
    "    text  = re.sub(r\"[^a-zA-Z0-9]\", \" \", text)\n",
    "    words = word_tokenize(text)\n",
    "    words = [lemmatizer.lemmatize(word, pos=\"v\") for word in words]\n",
    "    words = [word for word in words if word not in stop_words]\n",
    "    return \" \".join(words)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "df[\"Cleaned_Review\"] = df[\"review\"].apply(text_preprocess)\n",
    "df[[\"review\", \"Cleaned_Review\", \"sentiment\"]].head()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Feature and Target Extraction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x = df[\"Cleaned_Review\"].values\n",
    "y = df[\"sentiment\"].values\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Features shape:\", x.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Labels shape:\",   y.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Label distribution:\\n\", pd.Series(y).value_counts())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Vectorization"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer, TfidfVectorizer\n",
    "\n",
    "# Count Vectorizer — raw term frequencies\n",
    "cv   = CountVectorizer(max_features=5000)\n",
    "x_cv = cv.fit_transform(x).toarray()\n",
    "print(\"Count Vectorizer shape:\", x_cv.shape)\n",
    "\n",
    "# TF-IDF Vectorizer — weighted term frequencies\n",
    "tfidf = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=5000)\n",
    "x_tf  = tfidf.fit_transform(x).toarray()\n",
    "print(\"TF-IDF Vectorizer shape:\", x_tf.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "## 6. Count Vectorizer Implementation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6.1 Train-Test Split"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x_train, x_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    x_cv, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Train:\", x_train.shape, y_train.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Test: \", x_test.shape,  y_test.shape)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6.2 Logistic Regression"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\n",
    "\n",
    "log_model = LogisticRegression(max_iter=5000)\n",
    "log_model.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "prdt_train = log_model.predict(x_train)\n",
    "prdt_test  = log_model.predict(x_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Train Accuracy:\", accuracy_score(y_train, prdt_train))\n",
    "print(\"Test  Accuracy:\", accuracy_score(y_test,  prdt_test))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cf = confusion_matrix(y_test, prdt_test)\n",
    "sns.heatmap(cf, cmap=\"viridis\", annot=True, fmt=\"d\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Confusion Matrix — Logistic Regression (Count)\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Predicted\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Actual\")\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test, prdt_test))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "RocCurveDisplay.from_estimator(log_model, x_test, y_test)\n",
    "plt.title(\"ROC Curve — Logistic Regression (Count)\")\n",
    "plt.grid(True)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6.3 Multinomial Naive Bayes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.naive_bayes import MultinomialNB\n",
    "\n",
    "mb = MultinomialNB()\n",
    "mb.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "prdt_train = mb.predict(x_train)\n",
    "prdt_test  = mb.predict(x_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Train Accuracy:\", accuracy_score(y_train, prdt_train))\n",
    "print(\"Test  Accuracy:\", accuracy_score(y_test,  prdt_test))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cf = confusion_matrix(y_test, prdt_test)\n",
    "sns.heatmap(cf, cmap=\"viridis\", annot=True, fmt=\"d\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Confusion Matrix — Multinomial Naive Bayes (Count)\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Predicted\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Actual\")\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test, prdt_test))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "RocCurveDisplay.from_estimator(mb, x_test, y_test)\n",
    "plt.title(\"ROC Curve — Multinomial NB (Count)\")\n",
    "plt.grid(True)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### 6.4 Random Forest"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
    "\n",
    "rf = RandomForestClassifier()\n",
    "rf.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "prdt_train = rf.predict(x_train)\n",
    "prdt_test  = rf.predict(x_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Train Accuracy:\", accuracy_score(y_train, prdt_train))\n",
    "print(\"Test  Accuracy:\", accuracy_score(y_test,  prdt_test))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cf = confusion_matrix(y_test, prdt_test)\n",
    "sns.heatmap(cf, cmap=\"viridis\", annot=True, fmt=\"d\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Confusion Matrix — Random Forest (Count)\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Predicted\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Actual\")\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(classification_report(y_test, prdt_test))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "RocCurveDisplay.from_estimator(rf, x_test, y_test)\n",
    "plt.title(\"ROC Curve — Random Forest (Count)\")\n",
    "plt.grid(True)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
